 communities, noticing shifts in mood and circumstances more acutely.\n\n### Type distribution\n\n| Type | Approximate percentage |\n| --- | --- |\n| Generator | 36 % |\n| Manifesting Generator | 32 % |\n| Manifestor | 9 % |\n| Projector | 22 % |\n| Reflector | 1 % |\n\n## Legal Controversy over Copyright\n\nOn June 3, 2020, the Court of Florence issued an order stating that there can be no copyright over the Human Design system.\n\nThe order followed a lawsuit filed by Human Design Italia, an association claiming to hold exclusive copyright in Italy and in the Italian language, based on a license from Alan Krakower's (Ra Uru Hu) company, Jovian Archive.\n\nHuman Design Italia had sued an Italian publisher, Terra Nuova, following the June 2019 publication of the book Human Design – Scopri la Tua Vera Natura by Chetan Parkyn, arguing that no one other than Human Design Italia had the right to publish books on Human Design.\n\nAfter a summary proceeding, the judge ruled otherwise. In the decision, the court stated that the plaintiffs had provided no evidence proving they held exclusive rights over “the Human Design system” or its teachings. These teachings involve ideas, procedures, and methods of representation that can be freely discussed, referenced, and illustrated by those who are not their authors, without this constituting a violation of intellectual property rights. Nor is it necessary to be authorized by a school or its founders in order to do so, as under Italian law, the expression of ideas is free and not subject to sectarian control.\n\nThe principle, established under U.S. law and accepted by the Berne Convention for all signatory countries (including Italy), affirms that no copyright can be recognized over “an idea, procedure, process, system, method of operation, concept, principle, or discovery, regardless of the form in which it is described.” Therefore: “If Krakower cannot hold a general copyright over his ideas (as opposed to his specific works), then he cannot have transferred such a right to others.”\n\nAs a result:\n\n“The object of the transfer [from Jovian Archive to Human Design Italia] cannot be the exploitation of a copyright that does not exist.”\n\nAnd further:\n\n“Neither [Jovian Archive] nor its successors can prevent others from publishing additional [works] on the ‘Human Design System.’” [Quotes translated from Court Order: Ordinanza del Tribunale di Firenze: Verbale di prima udienza n. cronol. 944/2020 del 03/06/2020 RG n. 2756/2020, Sezione Imprese, Giudice dott. Niccolò Calvani]\n\n## References\n\n1. Sunil Bhuyan (4 July 2023).\"Human Design System: What it is, Types, Charts, and more\". beingawakened.com. Retrieved August 11, 2023.\n2. Goldsmith, Martin (2004). The Zodiac by Degrees. Weiser Books. ISBN 9781578633043.\n3. Can Healing by Human Design improve your life?. mnn.com, retrieved 18 March 2018.\n4. Hong Kong indie darlings My Little Airport back, more spiritual and just as political. scmp.com, retrieved 18 March 2018.\n5. Forget Your Sign, Discover Your Design!. HuffPost, July 26, 2009 retrieved April 5, 2022.\n6. What is Human Design?. oshonews.com, retrieved 18 March 2018\n7. Hu, Ra Uru (1992). The Human Design System. Human Design America.\n8. https://www.vice.com/en/article/human-design-meaning-what-is-it/\n9. Inside the Art of Human Design with Erin Claire Jones. Forbes, retrieved 6 August 2019.\n10. Schoeber, Peter (2012). The Human Design System. Human Design Services. ISBN 9783906187013.\n11. Parkyn, Chetan (2009). Human Design. New World Library. p. 17. ISBN 9781577319412.\n12. Burns, Anthony (2016). Ultimum Mysterium. Sixth Books. ISBN 9781785352614.\n13. Garnet, Mario (2011). The Wizard's Handbook. Balboa Press. p. 39. ISBN 9781452536125.\n14. What is Human Design?. oshonews.com, retrieved 23 March 2018.\n15. Curry, Karen (2013). Understanding Human Design. Hierophant Publishing. ISBN 9781938289149.\n16. Hustwit, J. R. (2016-04-26).\"Myself, Only Moreso\". Open Theology. 2 (1). doi: 10.1515/opth-2016-0018. ISSN 2300-6579.\n17. Stute, Petra; Würgler, Virineya; Würgler, Johnny (2021-03-01).\"Über den Tellerrand - ein Blick ins Human Design System (HDS)\". Journal für Gynäkologische Endokrinologie/Schweiz (in German). 24 (1): 50–51. doi: 10.1007/s41975-021-00182-3. ISSN 2520-8500.\n18. Scott Wilkerson on Human Design - Unlock your Life Blueprint and Chart. ahumandesign.com, retrieved 23 July 2023.\n19. Understanding the 'Human Design'. Fox News May 2, 2011. Retrieved April 5, 2022\n20. Stars Aligned, Part 1: Applying The Third Eyeball Test to the 2018–19 New Orleans Pelicans Roster Archived 2021-04-29 at the Wayback Machine. thebirdwrites.com, retrieved 8 August 2019.\n21. A Beginner's Guide to Human Design. Parade, 21 March 2021.\n22. What is manifesting generator in human design? Hindustan Times, 25 October 2023.\n23. Schoeber, Peter. The Human Design System – Type, Strategy, and Inner Authority. 2008, p. 304.\n24. Black, Beth; Bunnell, Lynda. 2018, p. 512.\n25. Rudd, Richard. Body, Mind & Gene. 2003, p. 64.\n26. Schoeber, Peter. 2008, p. 304.\n27. Schoeber, Peter. The Human Design System – The Centers. 2005, p. 256.","_meta":{"searchTime":8.832410000264645}}]}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_194prwpx2ry9_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: Human Design Certification — The Authentic Professional Path | The Human Design System\nURL: https://humandesign.school/human-design-certification\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n🌱Entry LevelHuman Design Reader & Guide CertificationGuide clients through their foundational Human Design experience. Type, Strategy, Authority, the nine Centers. The fastest path to professional certification.From $2,150 · 6–12 months →\n[...]\n🔬ProfessionalHuman Design Analyst CertificationThe complete professional credential. All 64 Gates, 384 Lines of the Rave I'Ching, Four Views, chart synthesis, relationship analysis, Incarnation Crosses. Four professional training levels.From $6,650 · 2–4 years →\n[...]\n📊Business & CareerHuman Design for Business & Career ConsultingApply Human Design mechanics to team dynamics, career alignment, organizational analysis, and executive decision-making. Ra Uru Hu's original business application of the system.Multiple pathways · Flexible timeline →\n[...]\n| Certification | Duration | Investment | What You Can Do |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| LYD Guide | 6–12 months | $2,150 | Guide foundational HD sessions (Type, Strategy, Authority, Centers) |\n| Coach Practitioner | 6–12 months | $2,347 | Integrate HD into professional coaching practice |\n| Ra-Direct Certificate | 10–24 months | $197/mo | Deep study of Ra's original recordings; foundational mastery |\n| Analyst Level 1–4 | 2–4 years | $6,650 total | Complete individual chart readings; professional practice |\n[...]\nThe intermediate bridge ($399 + $850). Required\n[...]\nFour professional training levels. All 64 Gates, 384 Lines, Connections, Cycles, Incarnation Crosses, Analyst Exam. $6,650 across 2–4 years.\n[...]\nHuman Design readings\n[...]\narnation Cross\n[...]\n- Business and team consulting: Apply Human Design mechanics to team composition, organizational dynamics, and career alignment for executives and founders\n[...]\n- Practitioner marketplace listing: List your services on the Human Design professionals directory — connecting with clients who seek certified practitioners in direct Ra Uru Hu lineage\n[...]\n-Direct Certificate Pathway is structured over 10–24 months.\n[...]\nFrom $2,150 for a Living Your Design Guide certificate to approximately $6,650 for full Analyst certification across all four professional levels. The Ra-Direct Certificate Pathway is $197/month. Use our Certification Cost Calculator to map your specific path and investment.\n[...]\nA Living Your Design Guide is certified to introduce others to\n[...]\nYes. Human Design mechanics apply directly to organizational dynamics, team composition, career alignment, and executive decision-making. Ra Uru Hu developed specific tools for the business application of the system. ICONIC's curriculum includes business applications within the professional analyst training track. See our Human Design for Business page for full details.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Professional Training Academy/Professional Analyst - IHDS\nURL: https://www.ihdschool.com/education-curriculum/professional-analyst\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Ihds School\nHighlights:\nThe Professional Analyst Education is a comprehensive program that involves three General Education Courses as prerequisites, and four Professional Level Courses, to be taken over three and one-half years.\n[...]\nPre-Requisites: IA Human Design Foundation Reading by an IHDS Certified Professional Analyst , and the General Education Foundation Courses: Living Your Design, Rave\n[...]\nand Rave Cartography.\n[...]\nThe General Education Courses, Living Your Design, Rave ABC and Rave Cartography, are the prerequisites for taking any advanced education program in Human Design. These courses give the foundation you will need before you move into more advanced areas of study. These courses are open to anyone with an interest in Human Design, not just those who intend to follow the Professional Analyst track. It is recommended that the student take a reasonable break between courses to allow time to absorb, process and digest the information - and most importantly, to have an opportunity to experiment with their Strategy and Authority.\n[...]\nThe goal of PTL-I is to develop professional level analytical skills. In this year long, three-semester course, prospective analysts learn the detail level of Human Design, and how to synthesize the BodyGraph. Through monthly study programs, and written and digitally recorded oral homework projects, students learn to integrate this detail into their surface level analysis skills. They will also practice and learn to Keynote, and learn the art of synthesizing a Human Design chart. Oral repetition will be stressed throughout to solidify competence, aid memorization, and develop chart-reading skills. Total study time is a minimum of 200 hours over the year.\n[...]\nRegular Price: $1150.00 (per semester)\n[...]\nThis is Level II of the Professional Analyst Training. Completion of all 4 Levels is required for certification. PTL-II is a two-semester program and is an interactive workshop that delivers extensive new content and approach. In the first semester, students will learn to give Connection (relationship) readings and the basic keys in relationship analysis. Students will be required to submit an analysis to demonstrate their grasp of the material.\n[...]\nRegular Price: $750.00 (per semester)\n[...]\nRegular Price: $800.00\n[...]\nPTL-IV is the final level of the professional analyst training to become a certified Human Design Analyst. The goal of PTL-IV is to guide and mentor you as you prepare for submitting your final reading to the testing Board for certification. During the course of the semester, we will work together on honing your reading skills. We will look at the structure and organization of your individual client readings.\n[...]\nRegular Price: $800.00\n[...]\nDiscount Price: $\n\n---\n\nTitle: Training Courses — Professional Human Design Education | The Human Design System\nURL: https://humandesign.school/training\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nFrom your first chart to professional analyst certification — structured programs with live mentorship, direct Ra Uru Hu lineage, and lifetime platform access.\n[...]\n🌱 Foundational Living Your Design AwakeningThe official Human Design entry point. Charts, Centers, Aura Types, Strategy & Authority — self-paced with lifetime platform access. $350 Enroll\n[...]\n🎓 Professional Human Design Analyst Training — Level 1All 64 Gates, 384 Lines of the Rave I'Ching, Keynoting & Synthesis, Four Views, Chart Analysis. The first of four professional levels. $3,450 Enroll\n[...]\n⬡ Professional Analyst Training Level 2 — Cycles & ConnectionsRelationship Connections Certificate + Cycles Certificate. Advanced design mechanics for client work. $1,600 Enroll\n[...]\n✦ Professional Analyst Training Level 3 — Incarnation CrossIncarnation Cross analysis in the context of the Quarter. Life Work certification for certified Analysts. $800 Enroll\n[...]\n🎯 Professional Analyst Training Level 4 — Exam PreparationFinal certification level. Refine your reading structure, prepare for the analyst examination, earn full Analyst status. $800 Enroll\n[...]\n🧭 Professional Living Your Design Guide TrainingCertification to guide others through their foundational Human Design experience. Direct lineage transmission from Ra Uru Hu. $1,800 Enroll\n[...]\n💼 Professional Human Design Coach PractitionerDemonstration-based coaching program integrating Human Design into professional practice. 10-session curriculum. Not a certification. $1,997 Enroll\n[...]\n🚀 Business AWAKEN Entrepreneurs!Human Design applied to business strategy, leadership, and entrepreneurship. 10 core worksheets from Life's Work to Profit Centers. $5,999 Enroll\n[...]\n✦ Professional Ra-Direct Certificate of Completion PathwayThe complete 8-level Ra-Direct pathway — study Human Design exclusively from Ra Uru Hu's original recordings, curated by Dr. LaVeena B. Archers. Prerequisites through PTL4 equivalent. $197/mo Enroll\n[...]\nThe complete certification track — 64 Gates, 384 Lines, advanced analysis, and professional practice.\n[...]\nWeekly live study groups and mentoring sessions across multiple time zones.\n[...]\n♾️ Lifetime Access\n[...]\nPermanent platform membership after enrollment. Return anytime.\n[...]\nCompletion certificates issued for professional levels. Qualifies for IHDS-recognized credentials.\n[...]\nPrefer to study directly from Ra Uru Hu's original Jovian Archive transmissions? The Ra-Direct Pathway maps Jovian Archive courses to IHDS curriculum standards across three tiers — LYD equivalent, Rave ABCs equivalent, and Rave Cartography equivalent — supplemented with HD synthesis labs and assessed with certification tests.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Human Design Analyst Training Year 1 — The Human Design System - Science of Differentiation\nURL: https://www.humandesignlifecoaching.com/classes-education-professional-training/p/human-design-analyst-level-1\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n### Leverage the most advanced human technology for transformation and growth to build a business you love.Professional Training Level I - Chart Analysis, 3 semesters over 1 year\n[...]\nThe goal of PTLI is to develop professional-level analytical skills. In this year-long course, students learn the detailed level of design and how to keynote and synthesize the BodyGraph. This course includes lectures, career workshops, study groups, and required assignments. Students will practice and learn to keynote, and learn the art of synthesizing a Human Design chart. Oral repetition will be stressed throughout to solidify competence, aid memorization, and develop chart-reading skills. This is a three-semester program. Total study time is a minimum of 200